	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=9782001095727>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9782001095727>Tip from Lvis</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9782001095727#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Dec 30th 6:16 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Trash him and start over!!! What ya need to cocentrate on is Dexderity and Charisma. Charisma will help your songs that affect crowd control and get ya better prices from the merchants( making you a richer Bard) and Dex affects how well you play your instruments, helps make sure you are not interrupted in melee and your chance to hit with weapons. I also suggest you take your songs after they are memmed and transfer them to the button slots in the bottem left of your screen. If you already know how to do this then bear with me since someone reading this might be helped also. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Left click and hold on the  top Spell Gem. A grey copy of the gem will pop off and attach itself to your pointer. Move your pointer down to the top left slot of the 6 empty hot buttons in the lower left of your screen. This is position  number one and you can cast/sing the song now  simply by pressing the "1" key on your keyboard. <br>Next do the spell gem below the first in the same way. Drag to the top/right  blank position of your hot key area. This is position number 2 and like the first one can be sung/cast by pressing the number key that coorisponds to that position. In this case when you press the "2" key you can activate the song/spell in that spot. Do the same for the rest of your spell gems down to number 6.<br>   Now here's where it gets a little tricky. If you are singing a song already then you must stop singing that one before starting another. To do this simply press the button twice for the new song you want to start singing. The first time you press it will end the current song and the second time you press it will start the new song.<br>It would look like this! I am singing the song in Slot one and want to twist it with the song in Slot 2 so that I can keep them both going. I press the "2" Key hesitate and press it again. This will stop song one and start song two. as soon as the second song takes affect I go back and press key "1" twice to restart that song. In this way both songs basically play continuosly, since there is a delay before a song's effects end after you stop singing. Hope this has been some help.8)<br><br>Lvis<br>Terris Thule  </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
